Prosternum 3.10 times wider than long (
Fig. 9
). Mentonniere distinct, narrow, prosternal process wedge-shaped, weakly convex, sculpture composed of coarse, irregular furrows.

Legs. Metatibia slender, inner margin distally curved outwards and coarsely serrate along distal 1/4 length (
Fig. 5
).

Abdomen. Ventrite 5 deeply impressed before apex, its posterior margin with a broad curved emargination. Submarginal edge of ventrite 5 projecting, roof-like, its margin weakly emarginate and indistinctly serrate (
Fig. 11
).
